fragment_downloaded_cb({"url": "design/bufferpool.html#shutting-down", "fragment": "Shutting down \nIn push mode a source pad is responsible for setting the pool to the inactive state when streaming stops. The inactive state will unblock any pending allocations so that the element can shut down. \nIn pull mode the sink element should set the pool to the inactive state when shutting down so that the peer _get_range function can unblock. \nIn the inactive state all the buffers that are returned to the pool will automatically be freed by the pool and new allocations will fail. \n"});